trend_summary: 1990s-style scattered houses evolved into wider, continuous ribbons of homes, especially south and east of the small airfield. Commercial blocks enlarged near the western highway junction, while several pasture plots shrank as cul-de-sac subdivisions appeared. Overall tree cover is largely stable and the runway persists, reflecting gradual suburban infill rather than rapid urbanisation.
notable_changes: Expansion of cul-de-sac housing tracts on the eastern side, replacing former pasture.
Western roadside commercial/industrial cluster grows and gains additional large roofed units.
Several isolated farm fields fragmented into smaller residential lots, reducing contiguous agriculture.
Minor extensions and realignment of local road network to serve new housing pockets
